JOHANNESBURG, November 29  – Several people are feared dead following a bus accident along the Kasese-Bwera road in western Uganda. Unconfirmed reports say about 20 people died after a bus belonging to Link Bus Services overturned at Kikorongo junction on Thursday morning. The sharp corner is considered a black spot. Bwera Division Police commander, Patrick Byaruhanga said that they are still verifying the casualities and the dead, the Daily Monitor reports. (ANA)